# Content Architecture

## UI text (`src/assets/contents/`)

- Store all user-facing strings in TypeScript modules under `src/assets/contents/`, not inline in `.astro` files.
- Organize by scope:
  - `common/` — shared UI (toolbar, layout defaults, popup labels)
  - `pages/<page>/` — page- or section-specific copy (e.g. `pages/home/hero.ts`)
- Export locale bundles as `UPPER_SNAKE_CASE` constants (e.g. `HERO_CONTENT`, `TOOLBAR_CONTENT`).
- Use `satisfies LocalizedContent<T>` for type-safe `en` / `fa` shapes.
- Resolve copy with `getContent(BUNDLE, locale)` from `src/lib/content/ui-text.ts`.
- Pass `lang: Locale` (not `isFa`) into components; derive locale-specific strings inside the component or page.

## Config & static data

- URLs, social link lists, and non-translated config use `UPPER_SNAKE_CASE` (e.g. `SOCIAL_LINKS`, `HERO_VIDEO`).
- Keep them in the same content module as related copy when they belong to one feature.

## External articles

- Store entries in `src/assets/data/articles.ts` (`EN_ARTICLES`, `FA_ARTICLES`).
- Resolve via `getArticles(locale)` in `src/lib/content/articles.ts`.
- Each entry: `id`, `title`, `description`, `url`, `platform`, `publishedAt` (locale implied by list).
- Platform labels: `src/assets/contents/common/article-platforms.ts`.
- Cards link externally (new tab); no on-site article detail pages.
